              <p>For allocators and family offices, Proto Axiom offers exposure to Australian biomedical company creation through a structure built for long-horizon translation, concentrated ownership and active operating involvement. For researchers and clinicians, Proto Axiom is a partner for the stage where a discovery needs to become a company. For universities, hospitals and policy leaders, Proto Axiom is one attempt to solve a national market-design problem: how to turn more Australian science into companies with the ability to survive the path to patients.</p>
              <p>We do not claim that every program should be built this way. We claim that more of Australia&rsquo;s best biomedical science needs an accountable builder. That is the role we are trying to play.</p>
